<item>
            <title>[AMQ-5883] AMQ accepts MQTT SUBSCRIBE and UNSUBSCRIBE with no topic filters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5883</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MQTT spec says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;MQTT-3.8.3-3&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The payload of a SUBSCRIBE packet MUST contain at least one Topic Filter / QoS pair. A SUBSCRIBE packet with no payload is a protocol violation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;MQTT-3.10.3-2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The Payload of an UNSUBSCRIBE packet MUST contain at least one Topic Filter. An UNSUBSCRIBE packet with no payload is a protocol violation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;OSX 10.10&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ckrey/MQTT-Client-Framework&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/ckrey/MQTT-Client-Framework&lt;/a&gt; testcases&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
